=begin pod

=head1 Grammar DSL

C<Slangify::Tutorial::Grammar> parses a canonical booking DSL line of the form:

=begin code
name "Jane" party 4 time 19:30 restaurant "Bistro Verde" date tomorrow
=end code

=head2 Token Reference

=defn name
Full name of the person, in double quotes. Accepts any characters except C<">.
Example: C<name "Dr. Jane Smith">

=defn party
Integer number of people.
Example: C<party 4>

=defn time
24-hour time as C<HH:MM>.
Example: C<time 19:30>

=defn restaurant
Restaurant name in double quotes.
Example: C<restaurant "Bistro Verde">

=defn date
Single word: C<today>, C<tomorrow>, a weekday name, or an ISO date (C<2026-06-01>).
Example: C<date tomorrow>

=head2 Using in the Slangify Playground

Paste the grammar into L<https://slangify.org> and use the canonical DSL as input.
The grammar parses standalone — no LLM step required.

=end pod
